<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Earth is the third planet from the Sun and our home planet</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Earth revolves around the Sun, but its average distance from it is 149 million kilometers / 93 million miles. In astronomy, this is 1 AU – or an astronomical unit.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Scientists have researched and estimated that our Earth is around 4.5 billion years old.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Earth formed at around the same time as the rest of our Solar System.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Earth revolves around the Sun once every 365.25 days – this is known as one Earth year.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In one year, Earth rotates like a spinning ball about 366.25 times – they are known as Earth days.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Earth is the fifth largest planet of the Solar System. It has a diameter of 6.371 km / 3.958 mi. It is the largest terrestrial planet. The other terrestrial planets are Venus, Mars, and Mercury.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The name Earth is at least 1.000 years old. It simply translates to “the ground”. The Greek name for Earth was Gaia – Mother Earth.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Only 3% of Earth’s water is fresh and 97% of it is salty.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The surface of Earth is covered by water, around 71%, only 29% of Earth’s surface is covered by land.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The mixture of gases commonly known as air are nitrogen, oxygen, argon, and carbon dioxide. Without them, we couldn’t live.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The atmosphere of Earth is divided into 6 layers – the troposphere, stratosphere, mesosphere, thermosphere, exosphere, and ionosphere.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Earth has the greatest density out of all the planets in our Solar System. This means it is very compact.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Earth has only one satellite – the Moon, but it also has a couple of temporal artificial satellites.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->
